@NODE "datasheet" "page_gc/datasheet (information)"


  NAME
      page.gadget -- a gadget for easy creation of GUI pages.

  SUPERCLASS
      gadgetclass

  DESCRIPTION
      Page gadget takes a list of BOOPSI objects and treats each as a
      single page of a multi-page GUI group. Used together with
      tabs.gadget and layout.gadget, it allows complex GUI layouts with
      hidden objects with virtually no work for the developer.

      This gadget class is contained within the layout.gadget binary.
      Thus, you will need to @{"OpenLibrary" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/exec/OpenLibrary"} layout.gadget, but not
      page.gadget.

  METHODS
      @{"GM_DOMAIN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 323}
      @{"GM_RENDER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 302}
      @{"GM_LAYOUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 318}
      @{"DTM_PROCLAYOUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/File" 288}
      @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}
      @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}
      @{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}
      @{"OM_DISPOSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 64}

      All other methods are passed to the currently visible object.

  ATTRIBUTES
      @{"PAGE_Add" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 365} (Object *)
          A BOOPSI gadget (probably a layout.gadget) to add to the end of
          the page list.

          Applicability is (OM_NET, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

      @{"PAGE_Remove" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 368} (Object *)
          Pointer to a gadget to remove from the page list. page.gadget
          will automatically dispose all attached objects when disposed of.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

      @{"PAGE_Current" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 371} (@{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52})
          Sets/gets the currently visible page. Note that @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65} will @{"NOT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1500}
          trigger a rerender, call @{"RethinkLayout()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/layout_gc/RethinkLayout"} afterwards. @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}
          will rerender automatically.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

      @{"PAGE_FixedVert" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 374}, @{"PAGE_FixedHoriz" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 375} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
          Like the respective tags of layout.gadget, these will, if set
          to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}, force the group's dimensions to the smallest possible
          in the respective direction.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

  SEE ALSO
      layout.gadget/--datasheet--
      ReAction example source for usage.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "PAGE_GetClass" "page_gc/PAGE_GetClass()"
@{b}

  NAME@{ub}
      @{"PAGE_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/layout.h/File" 46} -- Gets the pointer to the Page class.@{b}

  SYNOPSIS@{ub}
      page_class = @{"PAGE_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/layout.h/File" 46}();
      D0

      Class * @{"PAGE_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/layout.h/File" 46}(@{"VOID" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 24});@{b}

  FUNCTION@{ub}
      Obtains the pointer to the page gadget class for use with
      @{"NewObject()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/NewObject"}.  This function always returns a valid pointer so
      you do not need to check it.  The reason is that if the library
      opens fine, then the pointer returned is already setup.  (Of course
      this implies that if opening the library fails, you shouldn't be
      calling this.)

      Note that this function does not create the class, that is done
      when the class library is opened.@{b}

  INPUTS@{ub}
      Nothing.@{b}

  NOTES@{ub}
      @{"PAGE_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/layout.h/File" 46}() is contained in layout.gadget. There is no PageBase,
      just LayoutBase.@{b}

  RESULT@{ub}
      page_class - Pointer to the page gadget class.

@ENDNODE
